From: Joe Thornber <ejt@redhat.com>
Date: Wed, 4 Dec 2013 19:16:11 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 160/454] dm thin: return error from alloc_data_block if pool
 is not in write mode
Git-commit: 8d30abff758b5f6c71343b7da6bb5de129a76c08
Patch-mainline: v3.14-rc1
References: bsc#1020795

Signed-off-by: Joe Thornber <ejt@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Mike Snitzer <snitzer@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Coly Li <colyli@suse.de>

---
 drivers/md/dm-thin.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/md/dm-thin.c b/drivers/md/dm-thin.c
index 5f1b11e..1988019 100644
--- a/drivers/md/dm-thin.c
+++ b/drivers/md/dm-thin.c
@@ -923,6 +923,9 @@ static int alloc_data_block(struct thin_c *tc, dm_block_t *result)
 	if (pool->no_free_space)
 		return -ENOSPC;
 
+	if (get_pool_mode(pool) != PM_WRITE)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	r = dm_pool_get_free_block_count(pool->pmd, &free_blocks);
 	if (r)
 		return r;
